  <front>
   <head>ST. MATTHEW V. 9.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">" are the peace-makers, for they</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">God's children shall be called!" â€” so spake</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Prince of Peace, in mortal clay,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who veiled his glory, for our sake.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The stormy passions of the mind,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The boastful tongue and brow of pride,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Their soothing counsels, wise and kind</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Make to a gentle calm subside.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That eye upon the ground is cast,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Which glanced with restless angry glare,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That breast to hostile breast is prest,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Which thought to place a scorpion there.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Contentious tribes upon the ground</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Cast bow and spear at their charmed voice,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, linked in many a friendly round,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Will o'er the pledge of peace rejoice.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then flourish fields and gardens gay,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Where leaders charged with martial train;</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And Infants 'mid the herbage play,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Where lately lay the ghastly slain.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Blest are the peace-makers! for they</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To God's blest family belong;</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Honoured in this our earthly lay,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And in a sweeter, loftier song.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
